text:
An Indiana judge paused the first federal execution in 17 years.

The judge issued the freeze because family members of the convicted killer's victims wanted to attend the execution but saw their travel plans complicated by COVID-19.

text:

The vandal, who appears to be a white man, ran to the statue, scrawled his message in spray paint, and strolled away from the scene, as caught on video.

text:
